You can make a POST request sending a file using the Fetch API in TypeScript by following these steps:

1. Create a FormData object and append the file to it:

```typescript
const fileInput = document.getElementById('fileInput') as HTMLInputElement;
const file = fileInput.files[0];

const formData = new FormData();
formData.append('file', file);
```

2. Make a POST request using the Fetch API:

```typescript
fetch('https://example.com/upload', {
  method: 'POST',
  body: formData
})
  .then(response => {
    if (response.ok) {
      console.log('File uploaded successfully');
    } else {
      console.error('Failed to upload file');
    }
  })
  .catch(error => {
    console.error('Error uploading file:', error);
  });
```

Make sure to replace `'https://example.com/upload'` with the actual URL of the API endpoint where you want to send the file.

Additionally, you may need to handle CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) if the API endpoint is on a different domain. You can do this by setting the `mode` option to `'cors'` in the fetch request:

```typescript
fetch('https://example.com/upload', {
  method: 'POST',
  mode: 'cors',
  body: formData
})
```

This will allow the browser to make cross-origin requests to the API endpoint.

