To consolidate all tags of child models within a parent model using Spatie Tags in Laravel, you can use the `taggable` relationship provided by the package.

Firstly, ensure that all child models have the `HasTags` trait and the `tags` relationship defined. Then, in the parent model where you want to consolidate all the tags, you can use the `tags` relationship to retrieve all the tags of the child models.

Here's an example of how you can achieve this:

```php
use Spatie\Tags\HasTags;

class ParentModel extends Model
{
    use HasTags;

    public function allTags()
    {
        $tags = collect();

        foreach ($this->childModels as $childModel) {
            $tags = $tags->merge($childModel->tags);
        }

        return $tags->unique();
    }
}
```

In this example, `childModels` should be replaced with the relationship name that points to the child models within the parent model. The `allTags` method will retrieve all the tags from the child models and return a unique collection of tags.

You can then use this method in your application to consolidate all the tags of child models within a parent model.

